<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-22] shouldn&apos;t automatically set Content-Length in request header</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-22</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>currently, httpclient automatically add Content-Length: 0 in the request &lt;br/&gt;
header, this is causing problems with some web servers, particularly, with&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
ar.atwola.com&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Try the following URL&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://ar.atwola.com/file/adsWrapper.js&quot;&gt;http://ar.atwola.com/file/adsWrapper.js&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
It will block indefinitely. This problem can be fixed by not sending the &lt;br/&gt;
Content-Length header, this is the browser&amp;#39;s behavior. I&amp;#39;m not sure why this &lt;br/&gt;
casue problem, but let&amp;#39;s conform to a standard browser&amp;#39;s practice and avoid &lt;br/&gt;
troubles.</description>
                <environment>Operating System: other&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: Other</environment>
            <key id="12333581">HTTPCLIENT-22</key>
