                                                    <comments>
                    <comment id="12379250" author="marc.saegesser@apropos.com" created="Tue, 16 Apr 2002 04:36:22 +0100"  >Requests that do not contain a message body probably should not have a Content-&lt;br/&gt;
length header.  My reading of RFC 2616 is that the existence of a Content-&lt;br/&gt;
Length header implies that there is a message body.  The semantics of a message &lt;br/&gt;
body of length 0 may be debatable, but it seems reasonable to me to leave it &lt;br/&gt;
off.</comment>
                    <comment id="12379251" author="marc.saegesser@apropos.com" created="Tue, 16 Apr 2002 22:31:42 +0100"  >I changed HttpMethodBase.java to leave off the Content-Length header if &lt;br/&gt;
getRequestContentLength() returns 0.</comment>
